Boundaries are essential to set but can often be challenging to maintain. What is a boundary? A boundary is a limit or a space between you and another person. It is essential to set this to protect yourself and allow the other person to be aware of their limitations when engaging with you.  When healthy boundaries are in place, this is good for your mental and emotional health, helps you to maintain autonomy, develop your identity, avoid burnout, and influence other people’s behaviour.  When a person has poor boundaries, it means that in their relationships, they may have resentment, anger, and burnout.  Examples of boundaries:  Reasons boundaries are difficult to maintain: How to start setting better boundaries:  Practising having boundaries is super important. Make sure you set some healthy boundaries from now on!